      },
      "lineNbr": 278,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-09T17:53:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "DirectoryReader still logs a message and breaks the loop on errors, which is what we had before. The difference here is that this version falls through the loop on error, rather than an early return. I didn\u0027t collect the error because there\u0027s nothing more to do here but return.\n\nI suppose that might make it more of a problem if we add things after the loop though.",
      "parentUuid": "c225fbbd_a6beb51c",
      "revId": "9281dd0baf3511aa8e86a5ec2020df2e85d8e52b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
